:noun.  A game that is played between two sides using between two and six colored balls but typically using four colored balls.  The object of the game is to score wickets by passing the balls through the wickets in a particular order, usually in a set pattern going in one direction and then back through them in the other direction and finally ending at the peg.  The last wicket (or hoop) is called the rover hoop and is marked with red paint.  When all balls for one side goes through all the hoops and hits the peg the game is complete.